subsection.def:
bicycle (單車) means a
                vehicle with 2 wheels designed and constructed to be propelled by the use of
                pedals;

complainant (申訴人) means a person who makes a complaint under regulation 12AAO;
                        (20 of 2021 s.
                21)

franchised bus (專利巴士) means a bus in respect of which a franchise is in force under the
                Public Bus Services Ordinance (Cap. 230);
                        (3 of 2025 s. 6)

notice of rejection (否決通知)—see regulation 12AAJ(1);
                        (20 of 2021 s.
                21)

private car (私家車)
                means a motor vehicle constructed or adapted for use solely for the carriage of a
                driver and not more than 7 passengers and their personal effects but does not
                include an invalid carriage, motor cycle, motor tricycle or taxi;

public bus (公共巴士)
                means a bus, other than a private bus, which is used or intended for use for hire or
                reward;

road marking (道路標記) means a line, word, mark or device placed on, or set into, the
                surface of a road for conveying to persons using the road any warning, information,
                requirement, restriction, prohibition or direction;

traffic sign (交通標誌) means any sign, object or device for conveying to persons using a
                road any warning, information, direction, requirement, restriction or
                prohibition;

trailer (拖車) means a
                vehicle which is not mechanically propelled and is towed or intended for towing by a
                motor vehicle, including any semi-trailer or draw bar trailer;

paragraph.content:
a goods vehicle of a permitted gross vehicle weight exceeding 5.5 tonnes;
                    (L.N. 196 of
                        1984)

subparagraph.content:
(in the case of a franchised bus) when it is done at a designated bus
                        stop for the period required for passengers to get on or off the bus;
                                (3 of 2025 s. 10)

paragraph.content:
the Cross-Harbour Tunnel;
                                (18 of 2023 s.
                        15)

subparagraph.content:
the person stops and tenders to the toll collector on duty at the booth
                        such toll ticket as may be approved by the Authority appropriate to the
                        vehicle;

paragraph.content:
state the amount of the initial surcharge that is payable, in addition to
                    the unpaid toll, by the recipient within 21 days after the service of the
                    surcharge notice (21-day period);

state that any such notification and representations do not affect the
                    imposition of the further surcharge as referred to in subparagraph
                    (g);

state that the collecting authority is not satisfied that the surcharge
                    notice should be cancelled, and state the collecting authority’s
                    reasons;

state that the collecting authority demands that the recipient must pay, in
                    full, the unpaid toll and initial and further surcharges to which the surcharge
                    notice relates and which remain unpaid (unpaid sums);

state that if the recipient neither makes payment, nor gives notification,
                    in accordance with the notice of rejection, an application may be made under
                        regulation 12AAL for recovering the unpaid sums;

subparagraph.content:
the unpaid toll and initial and further surcharges to which the
                        surcharge notice or the notice of rejection (as the case requires) relates
                        and which remain unpaid;

a certificate, produced under section 14B of the Ordinance,
                        stating that, at the material time, the tunnel, for traffic flow in the
                        specified direction, was a boothless mode tunnel;

stating that the defendant was the registered owner of the vehicle
                            at the material time, and stating the defendant’s registered address;
                            or

paragraph.content:
must order the defendant to pay in full, within 14 days after being served
                    with notice of the order, the unpaid toll and initial and further surcharges to
                    which the complaint relates;

subparagraph.content:
a penalty of an amount as the magistrate may determine which must not
                        be less than the amount of the further surcharge and must not exceed $5,000;
                        and

paragraph.content:
